  "commentary": "With SPX at 6590.56 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6580 (-14.9B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+12.9B), dealers are currently in buy mode as spot trades above the amplifying 6580 level, creating upward pressure toward the 6605 resistance wall. The BREAKOUT regime with massive -43.5B total GEX means dealers will aggressively buy this move higher until hitting the 6605 stabilizing wall where they flip to sellers, creating a likely reversal zone. The gex_surge event combined with the tight 25-point range between max negative/positive gamma suggests violent moves are likely once 6605 resistance breaks or 6580 support fails.\n\nBottom line: expect a sharp push toward 6605 followed by heavy resistance and potential reversal.",
